===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|answere}}, {{m|enm|andsware}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|andswaru||answer}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*andaswarō||answer}}, equivalent to {{prefix|and|swear|lang=enm|nocat=1}}. Cognate with {{cog|ofs|ondser||answer}}, {{cog|osx|andswōr||answer}}, {{etyl|da|-}} and {{etyl|sv|-}} {{m|da|ansvar||liability, responsibility, answer}}, {{cog|is|andsvar||answer, response}}. Compare also {{cog|ang|andwyrde||answer}} (cognate to Dutch {{m|nl|antwoord}}, German {{m|de|Antwort}}), {{cog|ang|andcwiss||reply}}, {{cog|de|Schwur||oath, vow}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[response]] or [[reply]]; something [[say|said]] or [[do|done]] in [[reaction]] to a [[statement]] or [[question]].
#: ''Her '''answer''' to his proposal was a slap in the face''.
# A [[solution]] to a problem.
#: ''There is no simple '''answer''' to corruption.''
# {{lb|en|legal}} A [[document]] filed in response to a [[complaint]], responding to each point raised in the complaint and raising [[counterpoint]]s.

