===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|answeren}}, {{m|enm|andswaren}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|andswarian||to answer, respond, give an answer}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*and-||back, in return}} + {{m|gem-pro|*swarō||oath}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*swarjaną||to speak, swear}}, equivalent to {{prefix|and|swear|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{cog|ofs|ondswera||to answer}}, {{cog|da|ansvare||to answer, account for}}, {{cog|sv|ansvara||to answer, account for}}, {{cog|is|andsvara||to answer, reply}}.

